# Prisma Schema Rules

Every database schema change must:

1. Update `packages/backend/prisma/schema.prisma`
2. Create a new migration: `cd packages/backend; npx prisma migrate dev --name describe_the_change`
3. Regenerate the Prisma client: `cd packages/backend; npx prisma generate`
4. Update all code that reads/writes the changed fields
5. Update the corresponding Zod schema in `packages/shared/src/schemas/`
6. Run `npm run verify` to confirm nothing broke

## Safety rules

- Never edit migration files after they have been committed.
- Never use `prisma migrate reset` in production — it drops all data.
- Never use `prisma db push` in production — always use `migrate deploy`.
- Append-only tables (ActivityEvent, NotificationLog, AuditLog, UserBadge) must never have DELETE operations in services.
- All money/credit-style ledger patterns: idempotency key required, no UPDATE to existing rows.

## Local dev reset (when things break)

```powershell
cd packages/backend
npx prisma migrate reset   # drops + recreates DB and re-runs all migrations (dev only!)
npx prisma generate
cd ../..
npm run db:seed
```
